        <num>CC 1912</num>
        <heading>1912.  Aleatory contracts</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1912.  Aleatory contracts
A contract is aleatory when, because of its nature or according to the parties' intent, the performance of either party's obligation, or the extent of the performance, depends on an uncertain event.</p>
        </content>
